      • maskWith

        public void maskWith(Shape shape)
        Pixels set to black where they don't overlap with the supplied Shape.

        Holes in the shape are considered not to overlap. Only the filled in portion of the shape is overlapping.

        Parameters:
        shape - shape to mask with

      • maskWith

        public void maskWith(ShapeCollection shapes)
        Pixels set to black where they don't overlap with the supplied ShapeCollection.

        Holes in the collection are considered not to overlap. Only filled in shapes are overlapping.

        Parameters:
        shapes - shapes to mask with

      • medianFilter

        public void medianFilter(int strength)
        Applies a median filter to the image.

        Generally median filters sharpen and smooth the image while removing small dots of noise.

        The median filter behaves by setting each pixel to the median value of any of its neighboring pixels within the specified radius.

        The strength of the filter is the same as that radius. Usual values are in the range of 2-20.

        Parameters:
        strength - strength of filter
